Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report:

## **Comprehensive API Report: Microsoft.Extensions.AI and Microsoft.Agents.AI Packages**

Based on decompilation of the NuGet packages, here are the available APIs for building AI agents with tool calling:

---

## **1. MICROSOFT.EXTENSIONS.AI.ABSTRACTIONS (9.10.2)**

### **Core Chat Interface**
```csharp
public interface IChatClient : IDisposable
{
    Task<ChatResponse> GetResponseAsync(
        IEnumerable<ChatMessage> messages, 
        ChatOptions? options = null, 
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default);

    IAsyncEnumerable<ChatResponseUpdate> GetStreamingResponseAsync(
        IEnumerable<ChatMessage> messages, 
        ChatOptions? options = null, 
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default);

    object? GetService(Type serviceType, object? serviceKey = null);
}
```

### **Chat Message Types**
- **ChatRole** (readonly struct) - User, Assistant, System values
- **ChatMessage** (class)
  - `ChatRole Role { get; set; }`
  - `IList<AIContent> Contents { get; }`
  - `string Text { get; }` (concatenated text content)
  - `string? AuthorName { get; set; }`
  - `DateTimeOffset? CreatedAt { get; set; }`

- **ChatOptions** (class) - Configures requests
  - `string? ConversationId { get; set; }`
  - `string? Instructions { get; set; }`
  - `float? Temperature { get; set; }`
  - `int? MaxOutputTokens { get; set; }`
  - `float? TopP { get; set; }`
  - `IList<AITool>? Tools { get; set; }`
  - `ChatToolMode? ToolMode { get; set; }`

- **ChatResponse** (class) - Response data
  - `IReadOnlyList<ChatMessage> Messages { get; }`
  - `UsageDetails? Usage { get; }`
  - `ResponseContinuationToken? ContinuationToken { get; }`

- **ChatResponseUpdate** (class) - Streaming updates
  - `ChatResponseUpdate? Update { get; }`

### **Tool/Function Calling Infrastructure**

```csharp
public abstract class AITool
{
    public virtual string Name { get; }
    public virtual string Description { get; }
    public virtual IReadOnlyDictionary<string, object?> AdditionalProperties { get; }
}

public abstract class AIFunctionDeclaration : AITool
{
    public abstract JsonDocument? GetJsonSchema();
}

public abstract class AIFunction : AIFunctionDeclaration
{
    public virtual MethodInfo? UnderlyingMethod { get; }
    public virtual JsonSerializerOptions JsonSerializerOptions { get; }

    public ValueTask<object?> InvokeAsync(
        AIFunctionArguments? arguments = null, 
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default);
}

public class AIFunctionArguments : IDictionary<string, object?>
{
    // Dictionary-like access to function parameters
}
```

### **Hosted Tools** (for cloud services)
- `HostedCodeInterpreterTool` - Code execution
- `HostedFileSearchTool` - File searching
- `HostedMcpServerTool` - MCP server integration
- `HostedWebSearchTool` - Web search capability

### **Content Types**
- `AIContent` (base class)
- `TextContent` - Text messages
- `FunctionCallContent` - Function calls
- `FunctionResultContent` - Function results
- `DataContent` - Binary data
- `CitationAnnotation` - Citations
- `ErrorContent` - Errors
- `UserInputRequestContent` - User input requests

### **Chat Tool Modes**
- `ChatToolMode` (base class)
- `AutoChatToolMode` - Automatic tool invocation
- `RequiredChatToolMode` - Required tools
- `HostedMcpServerToolApprovalMode` - Approval-based

---

## **2. MICROSOFT.EXTENSIONS.AI (9.10.2)**

### **Function Invocation (Auto Tool Calling)**

```csharp
